{
  "name": "Hail of Thorns",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "icons/skills/ranged/arrows-flying-salvo-gray.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The next time you hit a creature with a ranged weapon attack before the spell ends, this spell creates a rain of thorns that sprouts from your ranged weapon or ammunition. In addition to the normal effect of the attack, the target of the attack and each creature within 5 feet of it must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes [[/r 1d10]] piercing damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><h3>At Higher Levels</h3><p>If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d10]] for each slot level above 1st (to a maximum of [[/r 6d10]]).</p><p><strong>Spell Lists.</strong> Ranger</p>",
